claim.claim-text:
6. A base station for providing a multicast scheme, comprising:
a processor;
memory in electronic communication with the processor;
instructions stored in the memory, the instructions being executable by the processor to:
receive from a multicast server, at the base station, information about a fixed multicast rate;
determine, based at least in part upon the fixed multicast rate, a fixed modulation scheme, a fixed protocol data unit (PDU) payload size, and a fixed number of PDUs per downlink (DL) burst for transmission of multicast data to subscriber stations, the fixed modulation scheme, the fixed PDU payload size, and the fixed number of PDUs per DL burst remaining constant from one DL burst to a next DL burst and from one multicast frame to a next multicast frame; and
allocate DL bursts to multicast frames, to deliver the multicast data to the subscriber stations via PDUs using the fixed modulation scheme, the fixed PDU payload size, and the fixed number of PDUs per DL burst.
